#  
job_list = []

page = 1

while True:
    URL = 'https://www.saramin.co.kr/zf_user/search/recruit?searchType=search&company_cd=0%2C1%2C2%2C3%2C4%2C5%2C6%2C7%2C9%2C10&keydownAccess=&searchword={}&panel_type=&search_optional_item=y&search_done=y&panel_count=y&preview=y&recruitPage={}&recruitSort=relation&recruitPageCount=40&inner_com_type=&show_applied=&quick_apply=&except_read=&ai_head_hunting=&mainSearch=n'.format(keyword, page) 
    response = requests.get(URL, headers ={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'})
    #response.status_code
  
    #print(URL)

    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

    no_result = soup.select('.info_no_result')

    #print(' ' + str(page))

    if len(no_result) > 0:

        #print(' ' + str(page))

        break

    else:
        div_tags = soup.select('#recruit_info .item_recruit')

        for div_tag in div_tags:   
            
            job_info = {}   
            
            # print(div_tag.select_one('.area_job .job_tit').text.strip())

            job_info[''] = div_tag.select_one('.area_corp .track_event').text.strip()
            job_info[''] = div_tag.select_one('.area_job .job_tit').text.strip()
            job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.job_condition > span')[1].text.strip()
            job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.job_condition > span')[2].text.strip()
            #job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.job_condition > span')[3].text.strip()
            job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.job_condition > span')[0].text.strip()
            job_info[''] = ''

            job_list.append(job_info)
    
    page += 1
In [ ]:
#  
page = 1

while True:
    URL = 'https://www.jobkorea.co.kr/Search/?stext={}&tabType=recruit&Page_No={}'.format(keyword, page) 
    response = requests.get(URL, headers ={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0'})
    #print(response.status_code)
  
    #print(URL)

    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

    no_result = soup.select('.list-default .list-post')

    #print(' ' + str(page))

    if len(no_result) < 1:

        #print(' ' + str(page))

        break

    else:
        div_tags = soup.select('.list-default .list-post')

        for div_tag in div_tags:   
            
            job_info = {}   

            job_info[''] = div_tag.select_one('.post-list-corp .name').text.strip() 
            job_info[''] = div_tag.select_one('.post-list-info .title').text.strip()
            job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.option > span')[0].text.strip()    
            job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.option > span')[1].text.strip()    
            #job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.job_condition > span')[3].text.strip()
            job_info[''] = div_tag.select_one('.option .long').text.strip()
            job_info[''] = ''

            #print(job_info)

            job_list.append(job_info)
    
    page += 1

from selenium import webdriver
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import time

URL = 'https://www.wanted.co.kr/search?query={}'.format(keyword) 
# Chrome   
driver = webdriver.Chrome("chromedriver.exe")

#  URL 
driver.get(URL)

#     
time.sleep(5)

SCROLL_PAUSE_SEC = 1

#   
last_height = driver.execute_script("return document.body.scrollHeight")

while True:
    #   
    driver.execute_script("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);")

    # 1 
    time.sleep(SCROLL_PAUSE_SEC)

    #       
    new_height = driver.execute_script("return document.body.scrollHeight")
    if new_height == last_height:
        break
    last_height = new_height

# BeautifulSoup  HTML  
soup = BeautifulSoup(driver.page_source, "html.parser")

#    
div_tags = soup.select('.List_List_container__JnQMS .Card_className__u5rsb')

for div_tag in div_tags:  
    
    job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.body > div')[1].text.strip()
    job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.body > div')[0].text.strip()
    job_info[''] = ""    
    job_info[''] = "" 
    #job_info[''] = div_tag.select('.job_condition > span')[3].text.strip()
    job_info[''] = div_tag.select_one('.body .job-card-company-location').text.strip().split('.')[0]
    job_info[''] = ''

    job_list.append(job_info)    

#  
driver.quit()
